    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-10-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="740"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d740">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-10-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 21, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Leishman reports that the schools matter is meeting with very strong
                    opposition on account of the great majority of the teachers being native, who
                    are always suspected of secretly preaching seditiously, and fears this idea has
                    been encouraged by foreign intrigue.</p>
                <p>Mr. Leishman states that he has refrained from assuming too aggressive an
                    attitude, and still has the hope that quiet, unwavering, and determined stand
                    will force a settlement within the next ten days.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
